			<description><![CDATA[<p>Finance Manager FP&amp;A</p>
<p>Do you thrive on a dynamic environment where you can be broad in your responsibilities?  Are you hands-on and detailed, yet have a strategic outlook that drives your work assignments?  Do you have the multi-tasking ability to manage both tactical activity and process and system improvements?     Then the expanding Aliph finance team is the place for you!</p>
<p>Reporting to the CFO, Aliph’s Manager of Finance is responsible for FP&amp;A and finance special projects, such as ERP implementation and process reengineering.</p>
<p>Essential Duties: <br />•Responsible for all facets of financial planning and analysis:   annual budget, quarterly forecast, monthly analysis of actual results, managerial reporting and  operational analysis.   ROI analysis on new customers and products, pricing and promotion analyses, product cost and opex analysis<br />•Partner with various business functions on continual reporting and analysis of the key drivers of the business, developing metrics and dashboards.<br />•Conduct competitor and market analysis<br />•Will work closely with accounting and operations groups on implementation of ERP system ----e.g.  Chart of accounts and cost center configuration; customer/vendor/part master configuration; developing key finance/sales/operations reports and dashboards.   We are implementing NetSuite and a bolt-on Rootstock MRP module<br />•Partner with Product Management and Development organizations on developing templates for product life cycle management process and executing those processes (e.g. Product Requirements Document and budgets, Engineering schedules and budgets, Product Cost tracking, Project status updates<br />•Participate in other projects as necessary</p>
<p>Skills: <br />•Strong technical accounting (financial, general, cost) skills.    Must understand accounting transaction flows and ERP configuration and coding.     Prefer that candidate have prior accounting experience<br />•Track record of financial and operational analysis that has driven improved performance of the company<br />•Process improvement/reengineering experience ---- this person will help build and scale our business<br />•Must be highly proficient with Microsoft Office Environment (Excel, Powerpoint, Project) <br />•ERP system experience preferred --- particularly involvement with implementation of an ERP platform<br />•Excellent professional verbal and written communication skills <br />•Strong interpersonal skills ---- teamwork, collaboration, influencing<br />•Able to handle multiple tasks in a dynamic environment <br />•Self starter: works with minimal direction <br />•Flexible and adaptable to changing priorities</p>
<p>Education and Experience:<br />•Bachelor degree in Accounting/Finance/Economics/Operations and/or equivalent years of applicable experience<br />•8 + years experience in progressive accounting and finance roles<br />•Demonstrated leadership ----supervision of staff and/or project management roles<br />•Manufacturing or distribution industry background a plus</p>]]></description>
