			<description><![CDATA[<p>Java Back-end Engineer</p>
<p>Aliph currently seeks an experienced Java Back-end developer to focus their talent and creativity on the innovation surrounding wearable technology. We are presently building an team who will be tasked with creating unique IP around the advancement of our future product offerings...</p>
<p>You might be thinking, what will a software developer like me do at a company like Aliph…they build headsets? Simply put - you will be instrumental in shaping the next phase of mobile communications. Aliph is building upon Jawbone to deliver the world’s best personal communications experiences. Aliph has a sustainable intellectual property advantage and a uniquely talented team to lead the company into multi- billion dollar business. With offices in San Francisco and Sunnyvale, California, the company is privately held and backed by Khosla Ventures and Sequoia Capital. <br /><br /><strong>Responsibilities: <br /></strong>• Design and implement high-volume, scalable and fault-tolerant back-end server systems.<br />• Develop expertise in the latest open source Java technologies.<br />• Gather functional requirements to generate technical design specifications.<br />• Contribute to all phases of our short (1-week) and long (2-3 month) development cycles, including app development, unit testing, bug fixing, deployment, and production support.<br />• Provide and adhere tobest-practices for web application development, develop/maintain server side applications, tools, and re-usable components<br />• Participate in self-starting side projects contributing to Aliph’s product offerings and growth. <br /><br /><strong>Qualifications: <br /></strong>• Minimum of 5 years of experience with JAVA, J2EE, ORM and Databases in a Linux/Unix environment.<br />• Proven track record of designing, implementing, deploying, and shipping high-volume backend systems for web applications.<br />• Experience creating and maintaining build and unit test systems.<br />• Understanding of best practices for implementating multi-language / international applications.<br />• Experience with one or all of the following a plus: MySQL, Apache, Hibernate, AJAX, JavaScript, Python, Flash/AIR. <br /><br /><strong>Skills/Experience: <br /></strong>• Excellent communication and organizational skills<br />• Excellent analytical and problem solving skills<br />• Experience working with cloud-based hosting services and external hosting partners<br />• Experience with disciplined software release build/deploy processes<br />• Ability to work on multiple overlapping projects<br />• Ability to work independently with minimal supervision<br />• Motivated by continuous learning and development, dedicated to delivering exceptional solutions <br /><br /><strong>Education: <br /></strong>Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or equivalent experience.</p>]]></description>
