			<description><![CDATA[<p>JDM/ODM Hardware Engineer</p>
<p>The ODM/JDM Hardware Engineer will work closely with partner companies to design and develop novel consumer electronics hardware. They develop original designs and monitor the work of our partners. They are responsible for delivery of the hardware portion of the product and will coordinate with a cross functional global team.</p>
<p>Responsibilities:<br />•Work closely with overseas development partners for new hardware platforms<br />•Act as point of contact to development partner.  This includes the ability to answer almost all detailed board level design questions that might arise at the JDM.<br />•Make product cost and architecture trade-offs working with Product Manager and other hardware architecture teams.<br />•Author detailed Hardware product requirements and specifications to enable efficient product development with partners.<br />•Review all product validation plans and test plans authored by partner and internal validation groups<br />•Review all product validation reports and test reports generated while testing the product.<br />•Work with compliance team to understand compliance testing needed for product launch into worldwide locations.<br />•Collaborative board level bring up with partners<br />•Component selection and qualification with overseas partners<br />•The applicant should be familiar with the design of portable low power products. Experience of a consumer electronics environment dealing with high volume and high quality products is an advantage, as is dealing with problems such as RF-induced noise.<br />•Duties include subsystem design reviews, prototyping, schematic reviews, prototype bring up and debugging, hardware testing, generation of hardware bugs, working with cross-functional teams on debug/analysis/prove-out and also some manufacturing test support.</p>
<p><br />Requirements:<br />•BS/MS EE or equivalent<br />•Experience with high-speed digital design (DDR, NAND and NOR Flash)<br />•Experience with RF design<br />•Experience with EMI and ESD management techniques<br />•7 plus years of experience board level design (block diagram to schematic to PCB)</p>
<p>Skills &amp; Experience: <br />•BS/MS EE or equivalent<br />•Experience with high-speed digital design (DDR, NAND and NOR Flash)<br />•Experience with RF design<br />•Experience with EMI and ESD management techniques<br />•7 plus years of experience board level design (block diagram to schematic to PCB)<br />•Prior experience working with large ODMs and JDMs in Taiwan preferred<br />•Hardware architecture and design<br />•Software architecture and design basics<br />•Excellent verbal and written skills<br />•Excellent team player<br />•Proven ability to lead local and overseas team to launch a successful product<br />•Experience with global regulatory compliance certification<br />•Experience with OrCAD/Capture CIS strongly desired<br />•PADs PCB layout software experience desired<br />•Low noise audio system design<br />•Experience with Bluetooth desired<br />•Experience with WiFi (802.11n/b/g/n) desired<br />•Experience with the following interfaces: I2C, SPI, and USB</p>
<p>**Travel will be required for this position, but will be held to the minimum possible.</p>]]></description>
