			<description><![CDATA[<p>User Interaction Designer (Audio &amp; Man-Machine-Interface)</p>
<p>Aliph, is looking for a creative, hardworking individuals to join us in making world class products. We have quite a few diverse and challenging projects that need your attention: if you love designing for an audience of millions, if you love the unique demands of software and product design (as well as marketing and web design), you might just be the right candidate.</p>
<p>The User Interaction Designer, reports to the Executive Director of Product Management and is responsible for designing user interactions for Aliph’s hardware and audio products that delight and inspire the user, are simple and intuitive to use, align with our visual brand identity, and deliver functionality that achieves our business objectives.</p>
<p>Our successful candidate has extreme passion for constantly pushing the boundaries of UI, while also leveraging tried-and-true techniques for building intuitive interfaces and maintaining user engagement. S/he can easily switch from understanding higher-level strategic business objectives to finessing interaction designs at a concept or detailed level.</p>
<p>Responsiblilities:<br />•Driving cross-functional and cross partner collaboration to integrate design goals and apply them to inspired interaction models that create genuinely seamless user experiences for our hardware products.<br />•Maintaining and refining clear, up-to-date user interface designs (e.g. command to button mapping, audio design, and ergonomic placement) that clearly communicate the intention and envisioned experience, based on user feedback and need for new features and functionality over time.<br />•Driving thought leadership in audio and user interaction design to create industry-leading designs that are fresh, unique, and differentiate our hardware products.<br />•Defining, organizing, and updating design principles, which can be leveraged across a portfolio of products.<br />•Working closely with product managers to understand the goals of the product and bring it to life in the designs.<br />•Working closely with engineers to communicate design intent while understanding the limitations of the technology developing workable designs.</p>
<p>Requirements:<br />•3 to 6 years professional experience with demonstrated success in building user interface designs across devices with physical interactions and audio interfaces<br />•Proficiency in Adobe Photoshop, illustrator, Visio<br />•consummate collaborator who listens well  <br />•Direct experience integrating all elements of feedback and objectives and able to dramatically modify designs based on the specific needs of the project <br />•Deep understanding of how to balance excellent design with timely deliver and is artful at making tough tradeoffs  <br />•Dedicated, hard working, capable of managing multiple projects simultaneously, exudes positive energy and is willing to go the extra mile for the company and the customer. <br />•Experience designing multi-dimensional interactions that span visual, audio, and tactile control and feedback</p>
<p>Education:<br />•BS Degree highly preferred</p>
<p>**All candidates should include a link to their portfolio or provide work samples as part of the application process. Please indicate your role and contribution for each project submitted.</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
